  "name": "Time Stop",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/magic/time/clock-stopwatch-white-blue.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You briefly stop the flow of time for everyone but yourself. No time passes for other creatures, while you take 1d4 + 1 turns in a row, during which you can use Actions and move as normal.</p><p>This spell ends if one of the Actions you use during this period, or any Effects that you create during this period, affects a creature other than you or an object being worn or carried by someone other than you. In addition, the spell ends if you move to a place more than 1,000 feet from the location where you cast it.</p>",
